                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/616: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dearing</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lisbon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-06T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >December 6, 1929—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Department’s circular December 5, 4 p.m.<note n="78" xml:id="d348fn78">Not
                        printed.</note> Government’s attitude is only of approval and willing
                    concurrence. Minister for Foreign Affairs telephoned yesterday, confirmed
                    statements to me of previous afternoon as reported in my telegram 42, December
                    4, 8 p.m., and said he was sending me copy statements Portugal is despatching to
                    China and Russia.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dearing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
